rComments: If you don't get stressed by moving deadlines and a bit of disorganization, take her class. However, her assignments did lack instructions compared to the TA's grading rubric. Also, it's the TAs who are tough graders, not her. You can ask for regrading. I can't stress enough how understanding she is with extensions. Kind and good prof overall.

Despite being very kind and attentive, this professor's lack of organization & clarity in terms of requirements for assignments made this semester VERY frustrating Deadlines were constantly being amended/changed due to not being able to adhere to the course schedule. Lectures were disorganized and inefficient. Assignment requirements very unclear.

Hands-down, one of my favourite human beings I've been taught by. She's a bit forgetful/scattered, but always moved deadlines to make up for it -- if that doesn't sound stressful to you, I would 100% recommend her for this course! Great prof who clearly loves her job, genuinely cares about everyone, and will accommodate you if you need it.

Despite being a kind lady and being recommended by previous students to ask many questions for the group project which is the majority of your grade, it is still tough to do well. Her marking is extremely subjective and unfair. Would rather have an exam. Her disorganization makes anyone anxious. Expect to be lost 90% of the time.

The group project is very heavy. Part one is 23% of your final mark and part two is worth 47% of your final mark... so basically 70% of your final mark depends on a group project. Honestly? I find her very disorganized in all aspects of this course, and is a tough grader even though she lacks organization on her part. Very disappointed

Can't use a computer. Lectures are 90% rambling and irrelevant vacation photos. Contradicts herself constantly and is unclear. Lectures seem put together 5 mins before class or sometimes during class. Completely incompetent as a teacher, regardless of research skills. Should know better. Waste of time and money. For shame. Avoid at all costs.

Very sweet lady but is confusing at times. Grading criteria can be a little muddy so ask lots of questions. Massive group project so be sure to pick strong group members. Made use of the textbook for most of the course. She brings chocolate + cookies to class a lot! :)
teacherRatingTags: ['Group projects', 'Accessible outside class', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Extremely disorganized. Moves test and project dates at her latest whim. Very kind professor, but only reads off slides. Online class page is impossible to navigate.

She's very unorganized and unclear in her lectures. The PPTs are confusing and need to be reviewed a lot to understand. It resembled a research methods class. No final exam, just one huge group project done over the semester. Tough grader. Nice person, cares a lot and loves talking about her dogs and grandkid. Answers her emails really quickly.

Late to every class, even to a midterm that she postponed. Postponed a lab for a month, was disgustingly unprepared when the day came. She doesn't lecture, she opens a blank doc w random titles, has students fill in blanks so she doesn't have to teach. Gave questions to write down to submit for project, gave a 65% on her own word for word response
What Kristjansson wants from students is constantly changing. UNCLEAR grading criteria. Ask as much questions as possible and write as much as you can in your papers.

I did well in her class but she is really disorganized, always late, and is constantly changing due dates and expectations. It's tough to find your footing when it seems like she doesn't have a plan for the semester and is just making it up as she goes.  My least favorite class so far at UOttawa.

The course expectation were not clear. She does not give helpful feedback. She is almost always the last person to enter the class because she is always late. She is very unorganized. She doesn't explain/teach things well.  She is very liberally biased when it comes to in-class discussion about current societal issues.  Worst teacher Ive had.

She is a great and sweet women. You don't need the textbook, but it proves to be very helpful for the group assignment and for extra clarity. You need to attend class, especially toward the end (there is not much on the slides). Make sure you have good group members because the main project is SUPER long and worth A LOT. Midterm was very easy.

This teacher is super nice. She is quite unorganized and gives different answers to the same question if you ask twice, leaving you worse off than before. Her exam was easy (I hardly studied), but the paper was long and painful. The first part of  the paper is group work, the second (discussion, results) is on your own.

Wonderfully sweet lady but expectations are very unclear for the unreasonably massive group project, and to add to that the grading was harsh. The midterm was poorly written and tricky for no good reason. Was late to most lectures, but that was nice because we could be late too. But again, very kind woman. But in terms of a professor try to avoid.

She is a very nice person, that being said, there can be a lot of confusion regarding expectations for some things, including the big group project at the end of the semester. Her midterm was easy if you did your work and showed up. Don't skip the class. She brought us Tim Hortons and homemade treats; very sweet lady but sometimes get confused.

Nice person but a somewhat disorganized prof (no offense). She accidentally posted the wrong grade file for our section. Also, test questions are not very fair (at least not the MC) and the class average was very low. Our final project was 104 pages!

Don't bother getting the textbook; you won't need it. The final project's a pain, so make sure you like your group members and can work well with them. There is no final exam. She explains things clearly. I really enjoyed her class, except for the project.
She's great but make sure to go to her office hours to get clarification and feedback on assignments.

Professor was extremely disorganized. Very vague guidelines and expectations pertaining to assignments. It was evident that there was little communication between her and the TA. Nice lady, but would not recommend.

Final project results were frustrating. There was a lot of subjectivity in grading. Hard to understand what you lost marks for. 12% of the final project mark was given to spelling and grammar, which would be fine except you lost whole percentages for things like "word choice". I understand it needs to be legible, but this is not an English course.

Underestimated her for the midterm. The project is a lot of work, but we didn't have a final so it was fine! There's a certain lack of clarity about her that is frustrating, especially when it came to the  project. Was late for most lectures. Very nice person though - likes to talk about her dogs. Responds to emails quickly.

Very helpful, very nice prof.  Always willing to meet with students, VERY clear in her lectures.  I actually feel I understand the course content/material very well.  I really recommend her for PSY3307.
Unorganized! Unorganized! Unorganized! Unorganized! FRUSTRATING! I think you get the point. However, she is very nice. She's apparently oblivious to her organization habits.

Always late to class, forgetful. Doesn't seem to know or believe in what she's talking about, but all her lecture notes are online. The group project is huge and a lot of work, and a little bit fun. However, she is a very, very nice lady who wishes everybody the best, and her exams are relatively easy with very few surprises.

She is a little unorganized at times, and often late, but she is really sweet and willing to help in any way she can. Her midterm and exam are straightforward- if you study the lecture notes, you'll do well. The group assignment takes a huge effort, so make sure you have a good, reliable group. I enjoyed the class.
unorganized, unclear, always late to class and when handing stuff back
Nice Lady. HORRIBLE PROF.
Smart enough, but likes to play dumb and sit on the fence a little too much.  A rather selfish teacher I would say.

Prof is a total sweetheart. Midterm and exam are only worth half your final grade. Two papers in that class which I found time-consuming. Also, the last part of the project is due during exam time, which is a real pain when you have 5 other exams to worry about.
NOT AN EASY CLASS - she is really nice, TA could have been better, the paper is time consuming and her tests are tricky.. you think you did well but just wait til you get your mark back..
What are you guys talking about?  Neither the midterm nor the exam was difficult and the project was actually kind of fun.  It is true that she's a total sweetheart.
Tough course but great prof, exam was too hard, but course was fair.  The subject is relatively uninteresting, and she does the best she can.

A psychometrics prof who cannot produce coherent exams? What's wrong with this pic?  Prof is extremely nice so it's hard to dislike her, but please, someone explain the subject to her, exams are brutal and w/final paper, the final was soooo not ne
